make Men in the Arena,

00:39:03.380 --> 00:39:07.150
which is a Teddy Roosevelt speech
that was given at the Sorbonne

00:39:07.150 --> 00:39:10.610
in 1910 that talked about
being engaged in democracy,

00:39:10.610 --> 00:39:13.520
and it's the critic -- it's not the
critic who counts, but it's the man

00:39:13.520 --> 00:39:16.980
in the arena, It's the people that
are in there, giving their blood,

00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:20.200
sweat, and tears, simply
participating.

00:39:20.200 --> 00:39:24.490
And that's what the Somali national
soccer team represented for me,

00:39:24.490 --> 00:39:28.880
was a bunch of young people with
impossible stories committing

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:32.520
to their national soccer team
and bringing all kinds of pride

00:39:32.520 --> 00:39:36.110
to a country that just
eats up soccer.

00:39:36.110 --> 00:39:40.540
Coming out to games any way
they can to see them play.

00:39:40.540 --> 00:39:44.050
And then Sa'ad and Saadiq kind
of taking this huge sacrifice

00:39:44.050 --> 00:39:47.250
to share their story, and
now they're in America.

00:39:47.250 --> 00:39:50.170
And it'll be a good six or seven
years before they could ever dream

00:39:50.170 --> 00:39:51.470
of going back home.

00:39:51.470 --> 00:39:54.160
But only because of technology
were we able to make this film,

00:39:54.160 --> 00:39:57.990
and only because of technology
are they able to communicate

00:39:57.990 --> 00:40:01.180
with their families and not feel
as lonely as they would've if,

00:40:01.180 --> 00:40:05.020 position:56%
maybe when you came over and you
probably have to get that phone card

00:40:05.020 --> 00:40:08.120
and make that super difficult
phone call once every two weeks.

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:10.470
So now they can Whatsapp
and talk to their families

00:40:10.470 --> 00:40:12.670
on a pretty consistent basis.

00:40:12.670 --> 00:40:14.370
That doesn't mean it's not hard.

00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:19.440
They have lots of days where the
trauma brings itself back up,

00:40:19.440 --> 00:40:21.080
where they miss home.

00:40:21.080 --> 00:40:26.040
But I think their journey
is really beautiful,

00:40:26.040 --> 00:40:31.700
and I think that's why I talk about
this being a first rough draft

00:40:31.700 --> 00:40:35.860
of Somali history, because I think
they're emblematic of what it means

00:40:35.860 --> 00:40:38.030
to be a young person
chasing your dreams inside

00:40:38.030 --> 00:40:40.280
of a super complicated world.

